= Kimodo Motion Generator (Remote) =

#type: node
#context: sop
#tags: kimodo, motion, ai, kinefx, animation

Generates 3D human motion from a text prompt using NVIDIA Kimodo,
outputting a 77-joint SOMA skeleton compatible with Houdini KineFX.

== Overview ==

The Kimodo Motion Generator node connects to a running
[Kimodo|https://github.com/nv-tlabs/kimodo] inference server and
generates skeleton animation from a natural language description.

This is the remote/resident variant: it targets a `kimodo_server` running
in resident mode (model preloaded — see docker-compose.resident.yaml) and
downloads the finished NPZ over HTTP, so the server can live on another
machine.

Press __Generate__ to send a POST request to the API server.
The resulting NPZ file is loaded and the skeleton is rebuilt on every
frame, driving 77 SOMA joints as points with KineFX `name`, `transform`,
and `localtransform` attributes.

== Quick Start ==

# Start the Docker services (text-encoder + api) as described in the README.
# Set __Prompt__ to describe the desired motion, and __Duration__ in seconds.
# Press __Generate__. Watch __Status__ for progress; the node cooks automatically
  when the NPZ is ready. Use __Cancel__ to abort a running job.
# Set the Houdini frame range to match the clip length and play back.
# Connect __output0__ to a __Rig Pose SOP__ (or any KineFX node) and use
  __output1__ as the rest skeleton.

== Parameters ==

Server URL:
    URL of the running `kimodo_server` FastAPI service.
    Default: `http://localhost:8001`

Download Dir:
    Local folder where finished NPZ files are downloaded from the server
    over HTTP. Defaults to `$HIP/kimodo_cache`.

Prompt:
    Natural language description of the desired motion.
    Examples: "a person walks forward", "someone waves their hand".

Duration (s):
    Length of the generated motion in seconds. At 30 fps, 3 s = 90 frames.

Model:
    Kimodo model variant to use. Default: Kimodo-SOMA-RP-v1.1.

Force Regenerate:
    Bypass the server cache and re-run inference even if a clip with the
    same prompt, duration, and model already exists.

Generate:
    Submits the prompt to `<Server URL>/generate` and returns immediately
    with a job ID. A background thread polls for progress, so Houdini stays
    responsive. When the job finishes the NPZ is downloaded to __Download
    Dir__, __NPZ Path__ is set to the local copy, and the node recooks.

Cancel:
    Cancels the job. On a resident server an already-running generation
    cannot be interrupted — Cancel stops a queued job or discards the result.

Status:
    Read-only. Shows the live job state: Queued, Running... (Ns) with elapsed
    seconds, Done (Ns), Failed, or Cancelled.

NPZ Path:
    Path to the NPZ file from the last Generate call.
    Can be set manually to load a pre-existing NPZ.

== Output Geometry ==

The node has two outputs, both 77-joint SOMA skeletons with polyline
primitives connecting each parent-child pair. World rotations are stored
in Houdini's row-vector convention (transposed from Kimodo's matrices).

:output0:
    Animated skeleton — rebuilds every frame from the NPZ file. Carries
    `name`, `path`, `parent_id`, `transform` (float[9] world-space
    rotation) and `localtransform` (float[16] local 4x4, row-major).

:output1:
    T-pose (rest) skeleton — static, does not depend on the NPZ. Carries
    `name` and `transform` (float[9] world-space rotation); joint
    positions are the SOMA77 neutral pose from Kimodo's skeleton definition.

Connect output0 to a __Rig Pose SOP__ for KineFX rig binding; use output1
as the rest skeleton for __Bone Capture__ or __Skin SOP__.

== SOMA77 Skeleton Hierarchy ==

{{{
Hips (0)
  Spine1-Spine2-Chest
    Neck1-Neck2-Head-HeadEnd/Jaw/LeftEye/RightEye
    LeftShoulder-LeftArm-LeftForeArm-LeftHand  [+ fingers 15-38]
    RightShoulder-RightArm-RightForeArm-RightHand  [+ fingers 43-66]
  LeftLeg-LeftShin-LeftFoot-LeftToeBase-LeftToeEnd  [67-71]
  RightLeg-RightShin-RightFoot-RightToeBase-RightToeEnd  [72-76]
}}}

== Notes ==

* The server runs in __mock mode__ by default (returns dev_reference.npz
  without re-running inference). Set MOCK_MODE=0 in the Docker compose
  environment to enable live generation.
* Port 8000 is reserved by Docker Desktop on Windows; the API server runs
  on port __8001__ by default.
* Results are cached by prompt + duration + model. Re-running with identical
  settings returns instantly (Status shows "Done (cached)"); enable
  __Force Regenerate__ to bypass the cache.

